On Monday, May 26, 2003, at 02:04 AM, Zach Freshman wrote:

> Who can tell me the difference between the cheaper EMPI Degree 
> Crankshaft
> pulley that I can get for around $30 vs. the Gene Berg pulley that I 
> assume
> costs a bit more??

I've heard of the following problems with "cheap" pulleys:

	a) don't seal properly, resulting in an oil leak
	b) not exact size/weight resulting in different cooling fan rates
		and/or load on your engine

i would assume the berg pulley would be less prone to these problems, 
but as usual, ymmv.

